Pulmonary infiltrates and fever in patients with hematologic malignancy: assessment of transbronchial biopsy. Pulmonary infiltrates associated with fever are frequently encountered in patients with acute leukemia or lymphoma In this prospective series, we analyze 47 such episodes in 43 patients. Overall mortality was 45 per cent in patients with infiltrates and somewhat higher when they also had neutropenia (55 per cent) or acute leukemia (67 per cent). Pulmonary infiltrates could be categorized into three roentgenographic patterns: local consolidation (55 per cent)